Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @pak choi{1}(trimmed), then separate the leaves. Cut any larger leaves
in half lengthways down the middle.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{}
or cling film. Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a bash with a
#rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2 cm thick. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Put the
@breadcrumbs{50%g} and @black sesame seeds{5%g} into another bowl and season
with @salt{¼%tsp} and @pepper{}.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely
coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging
> and discard any excess egg.

Pop a #large frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom
of the pan.

> You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins
> before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your
oven until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, give the frying pan used for the chicken a quick wipe clean.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the (now empty) frying pan on high heat.

Add the pak choi and @sugar snap peas{80%g}(trimmed). Stir-fry until just soft,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @udon noodles{220%g} to the pan. Toss, using a #fork{} to gently separate
them. Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, give the @itsu chicken ramen brilliant'broth{1%carton} a good shake,
then in a #large saucepan{}, warm the broth on medium-high heat until
simmering and piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes} - do not boil.

When everything's ready, slice the chicken.

Divide the noodles and veg between #bowls{} and pour over the hot broth.

Top with the sliced chicken.

Drizzle over the @Sriracha sauce{15%g} to finish. Enjoy!